        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 2:57PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Warrenton, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Warrenton, Littleton, Castalia, Macon, Centerville, Glenview, Arcola,
Medoc Mountain State Park, Aventon, and Airlie.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
